School Reopening Update for August 14, 2020.
Below you will find two updates for August 14th. The first is the First Day of School Tutorial for JVA and Group B Students and the second is the JVA Live Lessons Schedule.

name: Jville City Schools
tweet: Thank you for your patience and understanding as we prepare for a safe opening of school.

name: Jville City Schools
tweet: Students with the last name starting with the letters of “M” through “Z” (Group B) will go to school on Thursdays and Fridays. Please see Mr. Newell’s letter and The Learning Framework Options on the JCS website at  https://bit.ly/JCSReopening  for more information.

name: Jville City Schools
tweet: In Phase 2: Blended Option, students with the last name starting with the letters of “A” through “L” (Group A) will report to campus for face-to-face instruction on Mondays and Tuesdays.

name: Jville City Schools
tweet: Due to the high numbers of positive COVID-19 cases in Calhoun County, JCS will begin school in Phase 2: Blended outlined in the JCS Reopening Plan. The school district will temporarily be in Phase 2 for two weeks, starting on Tuesday, August 18 through Monday, August 31st.
